genealogies":"Genealogies","search.tab.images":"Images","search.tab.records":"Records","search.tab.secondary":"Secondary","search.tab.tree":"Family Tree","search.tab.wiki":"Wiki","search.tab.wikiLink":"/en/wiki/Main_Page","search.tree.ancestorFacts":"Source-Based Ancestor Facts","search.tree.browse.autoUpdateLabel":"Enter a tree title in the search field. Results will filter as you type.","search.tree.browse.collection":"Collection","search.tree.browse.collectionAndPeople":"Collection and People","search.tree.browse.description":"A searchable list of trees within the FamilySearch tree database.","search.tree.browse.filter":"Filter","search.tree.browse.infosheetSubtitle":"Collection Type","search.tree.browse.infosheetTitle":"Filter Collections","search.tree.browse.mobileColumnHeader":"Tree Title, Collection, and People","search.tree.browse.people":"People","search.tree.browse.placeholder":"Enter a tree title","search.tree.browse.results":"Results ({count})","search.tree.browse.searchInputSubmit":"Submit","search.tree.browse.title":"Browse Trees","search.tree.browse.treeTitle":"Tree Title","search.tree.familySearchFamilyTree":"FamilySearch Family Tree","search.tree.findCollections.autosuggest.label":"Select a Collection","search.tree.findCollections.autosuggest.placeholder":"Search for a specific collection","search.tree.findCollections.header":"Browse Specific Collections","search.tree.findCollections.paragraph":"In addition to the shared family tree, we have trees created by individuals, groups, and other organizations. Search for a specific collection you\'d like to explore, or view a listing of all of the trees FamilySearch has to offer.","search.tree.main.description":"Search the largest shared family tree in the world. Discover ancestors, and see where you connect.","search.tree.main.pageDescription":"Search the FamilySearch Family Tree for information about your ancestor. Discover new details, or add the information yourself!","search.tree.main.pageTitle":"Search the Family Tree","search.tree.main.titleHumanFamily":"A Family Tree for the Human Family","search.tree.results.title":"Family Tree Search Results","search.tree.sharedTree":"What is a Shared Tree?","search.tree.sharedTreeDefined":"Information people add about deceased ancestors is available to anyone who searches our tree. That is the beauty of teamwork. We might have discoveries already waiting for you.","search.tree.sourceBasedDefined":"Most profiles in the Family Tree are based on sources, so when you find the person you are looking for, there just might be a few records attached to them as well!","search.tree.unified.description":"Find your family tree on FamilySearch to explore ancestors, discover new details, and add information as you learn more about your family history.","search.tree.unified.familySearchTreeDefined":"The FamilySearch Tree is a free, shared family tree where people around the world work together to build one connected tree for humanity.","search.tree.unified.faq1Answer":"Enter the name of a deceased person, along with optional details like a birthplace or year, and click Search.","search.tree.unified.faq1Question":"How do I search by name?","search.tree.unified.faq2Answer":"Click the Find by ID tab, enter the ID number, and click Search. An ID number is a unique code assigned to each person in a family tree on FamilySearch.","search.tree.unified.faq2Question":"How do I search by ID?","search.tree.unified.faq3Answer":"Your ancestors may not be in a FamilySearch tree yet. They might be there, listed with different information from what you entered. Try variations of your search.","search.tree.unified.faq3Question":"What if I can\'t find someone in a family tree?","search.tree.unified.faq4Answer":"Yes. Most users will have the best experience by using the FamilySearch Tree. It\'s simple to get started. If you already keep a family tree in genealogy software, you can share it on FamilySearch.","search.tree.unified.faq4Question":"Can I share my family tree on FamilySearch?","search.tree.unified.faqHeader":"Frequently Asked Questions","search.tree.unified.pageTitle":"Unified Tree Search","search.tree.unified.titleFindYourFamily":"Find Your Family Tree on FamilySearch","search.tree.unified.userTreesDefined":"User trees are family trees created and managed by FamilySearch users. Tree owners share their research so others\u2014like you\u2014can view and explore it, while continuing to update and improve their work.","search.tree.unified.whatAreUserTrees":"What are user trees?","search.tree.unified.whatIsFamilySearchTree":"What is the FamilySearch Tree?","search.tree.whereYouFit":"See Where You Fit In","search.treelinker.tutStepFiveDesc":"The name on the left is a person from someone else\'s tree. If you\'d like to add this person to your own tree, click <strong>Copy</strong> and move them over.","search.treelinker.tutStepFiveTitle":"Copy and add ancestors to your tree","search.treelinker.tutStepFourDesc":"Your updates aren\'t complete until you click <strong>Save</strong>. Each item you copy or update requires this same step.","search.treelinker.tutStepFourTitle":"Save your changes","search.treelinker.tutStepOneDesc":"Tree Linker helps you discover relatives in other FamilySearch trees and copy their information into your own.","search.treelinker.tutStepOneTitle":"How It Works","search.treelinker.tutStepSixDesc":"You\'re ready to start using the tree linker tree tool to build your family tree. If you have thoughts or suggestions, click the feedback button to let us know.","search.treelinker.tutStepSixTitle":"You\'re all set!","search.treelinker.tutStepThreeDesc":"Compare the information about sources and copy any that strengthen or improve your tree.","search.treelinker.tutStepThreeTitle":"Compare and copy sources","search.treelinker.tutStepTwoDesc":"The person might already be in your tree\u2014but with missing details. Review the list of facts and choose which ones to copy.","search.treelinker.tutStepTwoTit